chara.textHome: I'm Suzune Amano. I'm not big on talking.
It's best you don't know my motives.
You'll definitely be...happier that way.

The one thing I can tell you is that
I don't think my actions are wrong.
That's all I have to say.

Since that day, when Tsubaki became a
Witch, I've refused to overwrite my magic.
The magic I use now is Tsubaki's magic.
Thank you, I'm stronger now.
I'm happy, though it may not show...

Yet another name to keep safe
inside my charm.

I couldn't do anything back when my parents
and I wandered into a Labyrinth,
but now I can fight on this level...
And I'll get even stronger.

What incredible power...
I feel unstoppable now.

With this strength, I can honor
the oath I made that day.

I can fulfill my sworn duty of ending the
Magical Girl system.

I won't yield to any opponent,
no matter who.
So, you're here.

Why are you so surprised?
Couldn't sense me?

Yeah, I happen to be good at hiding
my presence.
Even Incubators don't notice me.
Morning. Did you just get up?
Huh? Me?

I've been up for a while now.
I got used to it as a kid,
so I'm always up early.
Lunchtime...

Oh, I'm fine by myself.
I always eat on my own.
It's more quiet and relaxing that way.

Seeing parents holding their child's hand,
or two sisters walking home hand in hand
brings back so many memories.
I often had my hand held on the way home.

I'm on my way out the door, but
shouldn't you be getting some sleep?
Where am I going?

I've got...a little errand to do.
Don't worry about it.

I thought I'd look around Kamihama for
a while since I've got some free time.

You never know what info might
come in handy.

Defeating Witches and Magical Girls
are basically the same.
Both come from... No, it's nothing.
Let's go hunt some Witches.

I am very experienced in fighting
Magical Girls.
This will only take a moment.
No pain, no suffering...
It'll be over in an instant.

First you hear a bell, then a voice
will ask your name.

Answer and the Ripper will slice you
into pieces...
That's what they've been saying about me.

I'm planning to live at a newspaper
carrier next.
I'll have to do morning deliveries though...
No, I don't think it'll be too rough.
I just need to be a quick learner.

Want to read the paper? I've finished
reading, so you can have this one
if you like.
You didn't want to read it?

Don't tell me you've never seen
a paper newspaper before?
Curiosity killed the cat...

There are things in this world
better left unknown.

Incubators think emotions are irrational
and unnecessary, but we would cease
to be ourselves without them.

It's all the same no matter who my
classmates are. I'm not going to try to
get that close with anyone.
That's the way it's always been...
Something that I treasure?

Hm...I would have to say the charm
and bell on my hair tie.
Someone very important left it to me.

If it means stopping the whole
Magical Girl system...

If it will keep people from getting
caught in it, I'm fine with being "evil".

People can call me a murderer
all they want.

This is yours, isn't it?
No need to thank me...
I'm just glad you didn't lose it.
So...what's your name?
Farewell.
I'm doing the right thing.

After all these attempts...
the result's the same.
You can't win against me.

I didn't introduce myself, did I?
I'm Suzune Amano.
I'm a Magical Girl, like you.
What's your name?
I see I've gotten stronger...

With this power, I'll put an end to
the whole Magical Girl system.
You want to know more about me?

There are some things you're better off
not knowing.

I can absorb magic from the Witches
I defeat to use as my own.

But I can only store one kind of magic
at a time... Once I absorb new magic,
I can no longer use the old kind.

There was a time when I used to be excited
each time I learned a new magic,
to see what kind of powers I'd gotten.

That was back before I knew
the truth about Magical Girls...
